Team Agreement – Working Norms
Project Title: Tap and Pay System
1. Purpose of the Team Agreement
This team agreement defines the working norms, responsibilities, and behavioral expectations for all team members involved in the Tap and Pay System project. The goal is to ensure effective collaboration, timely delivery, and high-quality outcomes.
2. Team Values
The team agrees to follow these core values throughout the project:
Collaboration – Work together and support each other
Accountability – Take responsibility for assigned tasks
Transparency – Communicate openly about progress and issues
Respect – Respect ideas, time, and opinions of all members
Integrity – Follow ethical practices, especially in financial and security aspects
3. Roles and Responsibilities
Each team member will:
Complete assigned tasks within the agreed timeline
Actively participate in meetings and discussions
Share updates on task progress regularly
Support testing, documentation, and final presentation
(Role allocation such as Team Lead, Developer, Tester, Documentation Lead can be added if required.)
4. Communication Norms
Primary communication channels: WhatsApp / Microsoft Teams / Google Meet
Team meetings will be held weekly or as required
All members must respond to team messages within 24 hours
Important decisions must be communicated to all team members
5. Meeting Guidelines
Meetings will have a clear agenda
All members should join meetings on time
Action items and deadlines will be noted after each meeting
Meeting minutes will be shared with the team
6. Task Management & Deadlines
Tasks will be divided equally based on skills
Deadlines must be strictly followed
If a member faces issues, they must inform the team early
Delays must be justified and rescheduled with team approval
7. Quality and Security Standards
Since Tap and Pay involves financial transactions:
Secure coding practices must be followed
Data privacy and user authentication are mandatory
All modules must be tested before integration
Errors and vulnerabilities should be reported immediately
8. Conflict Resolution
Conflicts will be discussed openly and respectfully
The team will attempt to resolve issues through mutual discussion
If unresolved, the team lead or faculty guide will intervene
9. Attendance & Participation
Active participation from all members is mandatory
Absence from meetings must be informed in advance
Repeated non-participation may affect task allocation and evaluation
10. Agreement and Commitment
By agreeing to this team agreement, all members commit to:
Following the working norms
Contributing honestly to the Tap and Pay System project
Ensuring project completion within the given timeline
